Eye-Tracking Processed Eye-Region Image Dataset License
Version 1.2

Copyright (c) 2026 [Beijing Institute of Technology]

1. Scope

This repository contains a limited subset of low-resolution, processed eye-region images derived from an eye-tracking study.

The publicly released images:
- Contain only cropped eye regions
- Are downsampled to low resolution
- Have undergone processing to remove identifiable information
- Do not include facial regions or direct identifiers

High-resolution and raw data are not included in this repository.

2. Permitted Use

The publicly released subset may be used solely for:

- Non-commercial academic research
- Method validation
- Reproducibility verification
- Educational purposes

3. Restrictions

Users may NOT:

- Use the dataset for commercial purposes
- Attempt to re-identify any individual
- Use the dataset for biometric identification systems
- Use the dataset to train commercial facial or iris recognition systems
- Redistribute the dataset in its original form without permission
- Claim ownership of the dataset

4. Access to Extended Data

Access to high-resolution or full-precision data requires direct permission from the authors and may require additional documentation and agreement to specific data usage terms.

